spans.text: smile your lawns with vernal glories crowned , In vain gay Nature paints the enamelled ground
Where blow the winds , or heaven
in some wide and dreary desert lost
to climb , while hills on hills arife , In vain : or fall in tempests from the skies , Tread burning plains , or swim in seas of fire , Just reach the shore
view thee with a lover's eyes
the waking thought , or busy sleep
the tranquil deep , Nor lofty pines
Urged by the golden morn , the night recedes , And year to
with conscious pride each heart my own
this fleeting image of a day
earth her eye in sad suspense
what ruin Grief and Love have made
the neat labours of my hand
Ill suits the care of elegance with woe
my sorrows , hence with sighs I prove How feeble woman , and how fierce is love
my pain , Like the proud rocks which brave the unwearied main
thy infant food , But tigers growling over their savage brood
with thee through plains unknown to rove , Deaf to the dictates of paternal love
soul away , Fond , foolish heart ! to
the tale divine ; Why started not my hands when pressed in thine
Too well Remembrance paints the fatal hour When Love , great conqueror
silence all my weakness veil , And burning blushes only tell the tale
silence all my weakness veil , And burning blushes
sink to hell , and now ascend the pole
Now sink to hell , and now ascend the pole
his perjured faith the wretch shall mourn
how wild a thing is love
with spreading canvas flies , If these sad lines shall meet thy conscious eyes , And , taught with winning eloquence to move , The winds and waters waft the voice of love
Thy airy forms and glimmering shades
, why in lengthened pomp yonder sable train , With measured steps , slow
light the first great word obeyed
light the first great word obeyed
